	for writing, managing and publishing documentation.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>

    <para>This manual page documents the Lampadas Documentation System.</para>

	<para>The Lampadas Documentation System is a project of the
	Linux Documentation Project, one of the first and still one of the
	largest of all Linux projects. It is written by David Merrill &dhemail;
	and others.</para>

	<para>This manual page is not intended to fully document Lampadas;
	that would be far outside the scope of a manual page. However, it does
	list the documentation that is available.</para>

  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>SEE ALSO</title>

	<para>The scripts that come with Lampadas all have their own manual
	pages. They include:</para>

	<blockquote>
	<para><command>lampadasdb</command>, a utility to manage the data in your
	Lampadas database</para>

	<para><command>lampadasweb</command>, a simple web server that provides
	an HTML front end to Lampadas. An Apache/mod_python front end is planned,
	but you can use this utility for now.</para>	
	</blockquote>
  </refsect1>
